data.title: The food is good, but nothing special, and a little expensive.
data.text: I think the food is a little over-priced here, but I sometimes pay it because the location is so nice.  It's especially pleasant when a band is playing in the square on a summer evening, and we sit outside.  But there are much better places for Mexican food at lower prices.

data.title: Nice place
data.text: I gave El Patron an average rating because although they have good food, it is more of a fast food type of restaurant.

data.title: Great food at a great price
data.text: El Patron serves great food.   My wife and I occasionally stop here for lunch.  I love their Pozole.   I sometimes stop in for a glass of horchata or jamaica, and read a while if I am alone.  It is quiet, and a good place to have a conversation or meeting.   The service is great.   Photos of the dishes they serve are displayed on the wall near the cash register where customers place their orders before returning to their table to wait for the meal to be served.  The atmosphere is standard for a diner.  Art created by local artisans is displayed on one wall.

data.title: Good downtown burrito
data.text: Nice spot. Way more authentic mexican than the place across the street, but not as fancy. Good ol fashioned, simple, reasonably priced, mexican fare.
